result.adr_address: 12A號 Elgin St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: The Noodle Hive

reviews.text:
The noodles here are thinner than expected but it is more chewy to me, I like them! 
Ordered 3 toppings with noodles ($52)and cold lychee vinegar honey($28)which is also very enjoyable under this rainy cloudy day. 
The noodles is served with sauce and Japanese soup, I firstly put sauce onto the noodles. After finishing half of it, put the soup into the noodles bowl. 
Wow, the taste of the soup mixed with the sauce is totally different and  amazing! It really surprised me, highly recommended, especially for those walk nearby SoHo district and don't wanna spend a lot.

Quite a special place in Hong Kong for noodles of your choice but I have to say. If you are not working around this neighbourhood; you might have trouble locating it. I walk to the front door 3 times until I find the place.

Their noodles are good and charges with a fair enough price. You can pick the noodles, sides and soup by your own choice or you can just choose from the sets that are already recommended by the shop.

It is actually quite a fusion-ed local/traditional store but I personally don't enjoy so much eating in this place.

Best noodles of this fusion type in Central. The shop is located above Hollywood Road in the heart of Soho.
It combines the traditional elements of Hong Kong cart noodles with Asian cuisine and soups. 
The options in sauces for noodles are innovative. Like the iced lemon tea the most. 
The opening hours are not stable yet.
I wish it keeps surviving in Central.
Very nice. Noodles and the ingredients taste really nice with the sauce and pour in the soup afterwards.
Food was flavorful, big portions, reasonably priced. Everything tasted very fresh and clean, helpful staff

This was a great area for sightseeing and taking a walk. There are an amazing assortment of restaurants and stores along the way. We ate at a little hole in the wall Vietnamese restaurant that was absolutely awesome.

This neighbourhood has a couple of murals that are well known to tourists, (ex. The one pictured here as well as the brooklyn mural). It is a great place for taking photos; however, I would recommend for future visitors to arrive earlier to take pictures (11:30 am latest) because it will get pretty crowded at the murals after noon.

Good area in Hong Kong overall to go out and chill -whether you prefer that be over good food, drinks or both. Some places here also show sports games, and there are plenty of cuisines represented. Do prepare to spend a bit more, and getting around in the crowd here can be tiring, or nearly impossible if you have mobility restrictions.
Such a great vibe. Lots of great bars. Very western environment not what you would imagine HK to be like.
Soho is a little upscale part of LKF central. Most Western locals go here. You will have fun!
